## Task

Create render system that only renders visible lines from VirtualViewport.

## System Design

```typescript
function virtualizedRenderSystem(world: World): World {
  const entities = virtualizedQuery(world);

  for (const eid of entities) {
    const viewport = getVirtualViewport(world, eid);
    const store = getLineStore(eid);
    const position = getPosition(world, eid);
    const dimensions = getDimensions(world, eid);

    // Only get visible lines from store
    const visibleLines = store.getLines(
      viewport.firstVisibleLine,
      viewport.visibleLineCount + viewport.overscan
    );

    // Render only visible lines to screen buffer
    for (let i = 0; i < visibleLines.length; i++) {
      renderLine(
        position.x,
        position.y + i,
        visibleLines[i],
        dimensions.width
      );
    }
  }

  return world;
}
```

## Integration

- Works with existing screen buffer
- Respects Position and Dimensions components
- Applies Renderable styles (fg/bg colors)
- Handles Border component (adjusts content area)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Only renders visible lines (verify with profiler)
- [ ] 60fps scroll performance with 10M lines
- [ ] Integrates with existing render pipeline
- [ ] Overscan prevents flicker during fast scroll

## Task

Create efficient storage for millions of text lines, separate from the ECS typed arrays.

## Design

```typescript
interface VirtualizedLineStore {
  // Core operations
  getLine(index: number): string;
  getLines(start: number, count: number): string[];
  getLineCount(): number;

  // Modification
  setLines(lines: string[]): void;
  appendLine(line: string): void;
  appendLines(lines: string[]): void;

  // Bulk operations
  clear(): void;

  // Memory management
  getMemoryUsage(): number;
}
```

## Implementation

Use line index approach for v1:
- Single ArrayBuffer for all text (UTF-8 encoded)
- Uint32Array of byte offsets for line starts
- TextDecoder for extracting lines

## Performance Requirements

- getLine(n): O(1)
- appendLine(): O(1) amortized
- Memory: ~1 byte per char + 4 bytes per line overhead

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Store 10M lines without crash
- [ ] getLine returns in <1ms for any index
- [ ] appendLine handles 1000 calls/sec
- [ ] Memory usage matches estimates
- [ ] Full test coverage

