description:
## Task

Create high-level widget wrapping virtualized components.

## Widget API

```typescript
interface VirtualizedListConfig {
  x: number | string;
  y: number | string;
  width: number | string;
  height: number | string;

  // Initial content
  lines?: string[];

  // Behavior
  mouse?: boolean;        // Enable mouse wheel scrolling
  keys?: boolean;         // Enable keyboard scrolling

  // Styling
  style?: StyleOptions;
  border?: BorderOptions;

  // Performance
  overscan?: number;      // Extra lines to render (default: 3)
}

// Factory
const list = game.createVirtualizedList(config);

// Methods
list.setLines(lines: string[]): VirtualizedList;
list.appendLine(line: string): VirtualizedList;
list.appendLines(lines: string[]): VirtualizedList;
list.scrollToLine(n: number): VirtualizedList;
list.scrollToTop(): VirtualizedList;
list.scrollToBottom(): VirtualizedList;
list.getLineCount(): number;
list.clear(): VirtualizedList;

// For log viewers
list.follow(enabled: boolean): VirtualizedList;  // Auto-scroll on append
```

## Use Cases

1. **Log Viewer**
   ```typescript
   const log = game.createVirtualizedList({ ... });
   log.follow(true);
   process.stdout.on('data', (line) => log.appendLine(line));
   ```

2. **Large File Viewer**
   ```typescript
   const viewer = game.createVirtualizedList({ ... });
   viewer.setLines(fs.readFileSync('huge.log', 'utf8').split('\n'));
   ```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Widget follows blECSd patterns
- [ ] Handles 10M+ lines
- [ ] Mouse wheel scrolling
- [ ] Keyboard navigation (arrows, page up/down, home/end)
- [ ] Follow mode for streaming
- [ ] Full test coverage
- [ ] API docs page

Create PNG file parser for image rendering.

Port tng.js PNG parsing.

Tasks:
1. Create src/media/png/parser.ts
2. Implement PNG parsing:
   - Validate PNG magic bytes
   - Parse chunk structure (length, type, data, CRC)
   - Handle chunk types: IHDR, PLTE, IDAT, IEND, tRNS, acTL, fcTL, fdAT

3. Create interfaces:
```typescript
interface PNGHeader {
  width: number;
  height: number;
  bitDepth: number;
  colorType: ColorType;
  compression: number;
  filter: number;
  interlace: boolean;
}

